# Phase 3 Stage 1 Fast Path

- Keep exactly one active error and queue all new earlier failures as candidates.
- Before any new conclusion, identify the last proven checkpoint on this ladder:
  `0x0001 -> 0x00f0 -> 0x0030 -> 0x003c -> before_LoadModelFromFile -> after_LoadModelFromFile -> before_NewContextWithModel -> before_backend_graph_reserve i=1 -> after_backend_graph_reserve i=1 -> before_backend_graph_reserve i=2 -> after_backend_graph_reserve i=2 -> HTTP 200 -> residency`.
- Change only one layer per cycle: host QEMU stub, mediator, guest shim, Ollama binary/shared libs, or runtime config.
- After every deploy, prove the live artifact path before interpreting runtime behavior.
- Use one clean bounded repro payload and the same trace set until the active error changes.
- If a run fails earlier than the last proven checkpoint, classify it as a regression and repair that baseline first.
- Do not reopen already-solved endpoint/bootstrap branches unless the checkpoint ladder genuinely falls earlier again.
- Do not run the full Stage 1 gate while the active blocker is still earlier than the milestone path.
- `Plan A` is the preserved checked-in canary: `qwen2.5:0.5b` plus the default `phase1_milestone_gate.py` and `phase1_milestone_test_suite.json`.
- `Plan B` is the explicit Phase 1 advancement branch: `tinyllama:latest` unless the user redefines the target.
- Preserve `Plan A` before and after risky `Plan B` work; if `Plan A` regresses, stop and repair it first.
- Do not claim full Phase 1 completion from `Plan A` alone while `Plan B` remains an explicit milestone target.
- If `Plan B` fails while `Plan A` passes, classify the earliest failing `Plan B` checkpoint and keep `Plan A` frozen as the recovery baseline.
